ations to a Special school all have statements. I don't know if it is the same for every special school, but if you have a child in a special school around here, the parents have to apply for a place for their child each year. So once you have been accepted that does not mean that they just stay there until the age of leaving. A place has to be applied for annually. &#10;In answer to your other question, no I didn't have any input as to selecting the 1:1 for him. I would let them know if the 1:1 is not working out though, and there has been changes over the years. &#10;And its a pleasure to help you...... so let me know if you want any more help. xx"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="956" language="en" documentId="4962" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Julie C(396)" date="04-04-10 15:21" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/netmums-coffeehouse-archives-528/primary-school-admission-appeals-clinic-599/404307-special-educational-needs-re-mainstream-school-all.html" topic="mainstreaming" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4962" notes="" title="Special Educational Needs re. Mainstream school"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="676"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="677" end="874"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="875" end="956"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>